.SH NAME
\*LSgThumbWheelSetValue \*O\(em A ThumbWheel function that sets the wheel value
.iX "SgThumbWheelSetValue"
.iX "Scale functions" "SgThumbWheelSetValue"
.SH SYNOPSIS
.sS
.iS
\&#include <Sgm/ThumbWheel.h>
.sp \n(PDu
void SgThumbWheelSetValue (\*Vwidget, value\*L)
.ta .5i 1.5i
	Widget	\*Vwidget\*L;
	int	\*Vvalue\*L;
.wH .fi
.iE
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
\*LSgThumbWheelSetValue\*O sets the thumb wheel \*Vvalue\*O within the
ThumbWheel widget.
It is equivalent to setting \*LXmNvalue\*O resource through
\*LXtSetValues\*O, except that it does not clear the window before
redrawing, and therefore causes less visual "flicker".
.VL 1i 
.LI "\*Vwidget\*O"
Specifies the ThumbWheel widget ID.
.LI "\*Vvalue\*O"
Specifies the wheel position.
This sets the \*LXmNvalue\*O resource.
.LE 
.PP 
For a complete definition of Scale and its associated resources, see
\*LSgThumbWheel(3X)\*O.
.SH RELATED INFORMATION
.na
